credit.credit-words: Come, ye sons of human race, In this chorus take you place; And amid the mortal throng Be ye masters of the song. Let, in praise of God, the sound Run a never-ending round. That our song of praise may be Everlasting, as is He.
Come, O come, in pious lays

direction-type.words: So, from heaven on earth He shall
And this huge wide orb we see
Shall one choir, one temple be;
All the bounds of place and time.
And ascend from sphere to sphere
